'''Cornelius the First''' (died April 3, 2013)<ref name = "KLTV">{{cite news|url = http://www.kltv.com/story/22042159/caldwell-zoos-black-rhino-cornelius-has-died|title = Caldwell Zoo's black rhino Cornelius has died|author = Kerri Compton|publisher = KLTV|date = April 22, 2013}}</ref> was a [[black rhinoceros]] at the [[Granby Zoo]] in [[Granby, Quebec]], Canada. The name "Cornelius" is a French-language [[pun]], as the French word for "horn" is ''corne''.
==Political candidature== Cornelius was the nominal leader of the [[List of federal political parties in Canada|federal political party]], the [[Rhinoceros Party of Canada (1963–1993)|Rhinoceros Party of Canada]] from 1965 to 1993. The party attracted a considerable number of votes in Canadian elections [[Canadian federal election, 1979|1979]], [[Canadian federal election, 1980|1980]] and [[Canadian federal election, 1984|1984]], sometimes even coming in second place in some [[electoral district (Canada)|riding]]s, but never elected a candidate to the [[House of Commons of Canada]].
The Party was inspired by [[Non-human electoral candidates|Cacareco]], a rhinoceros at the [[São Paulo]] zoo in Brazil, which was a candidate for the 1958 city council elections with the intention of protesting against political corruption.<ref>[http://www.memoriaviva.com.br/ocruzeiro/24101959/241059_8.htm Cacareco]</ref> Electoral officials did not accept Cacareco's candidacy, but he eventually won 100,000 votes, more than any other party in that same election (which was also marked by rampant [[absenteeism]]). Today, the term "Voto Cacareco" (Cacareco vote) is commonly used to describe protest votes in Brazil.
During the [[Canadian federal election, 1984|Canadian federal election of 1984]], the party made a major part of their platform declaring war on [[Belgium]] because a Belgian cartoon character, ''[[The Adventures of Tintin|Tintin]]'', killed a rhinoceros in one of the early works of the comics series.<ref name="FORCES">{{Cite web |url=http://www.forces.org/canada/news-archive/092003.htm |title=Dateline-Montreal Grand Prix update |publisher=[[Forces Canada]] |date=September 5, 2003 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070625142517/http://www.forces.org/canada/news-archive/092003.htm |archivedate=2007-06-25 |df= }}</ref> The party offered to call off the threatened Belgium-Canada war if Belgium delivered a case of [[mussels]] and a case of Belgian beer to Rhinoceros "Hindquarters" in Montreal (the Belgian Embassy in Ottawa ''did'', in fact, do this).<ref name = "FORCES" />
==United States== The Granby Zoo eventually traded Cornelius to the [[San Diego Zoo]] in exchange for a [[giraffe]].<ref>{{cite news|url = https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/after-years-of-near-extinction-the-whacky-rhino-party-is-back/article18142763/|title = After years of near-extinction, the whacky Rhino party is back|author = Ingrid Peritz|publisher = The Globe and Mail|date = August 8, 2007}}</ref> The San Diego Zoo loaned him to the [[Caldwell Zoo]], where he fathered an offspring on January 6, 2003.<ref>{{cite journal|url = http://www.aza.org/Publications/2003/04/April2003SigEffortsCons.pdf|title = Black Rhino Born at Caldwell Zoo|journal = Significant Efforts in Conservation|date = April 2003|publisher = Association of Zoos and Aquariums|format = PDF|deadurl = yes|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070221141808/http://www.aza.org/Publications/2003/04/April2003SigEffortsCons.pdf|archivedate = 2007-02-21|df = }}</ref>
==Death== Cornelius died on April 3, 2013, at the Caldwell Zoo. A news report indicated he "was suffering from pneumonia and [[mycobacterium tuberculosis complex]] was present in his lungs".<ref name = "KLTV" />
